HEADWORD: Triplite
<hw>Trip"lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>triplite</ets>. See <er>Triple</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a dark brown color, generally with a fibrous, massive
structure. It is a fluophosphate of iron and manganese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triploblastic</ent>⟦br⟧
